<br>
&quot;Oh God what have I done,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Silvereyes spoke in a whisper.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Not again, how could it come to this?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A low rumble ran across the floor as her knees hit the blackened marble and she began to weep, covering her face with her hands.  Blood trickled from them, smearing across her face and clothes, she couldn't breathe.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
  &quot;Please, this can't happen, not again.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Silvereyes pleaded in her mind.  Her guild, her family, her home.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Then quietly, a soft breeze began to blow through the dark night sky, into the room, a whisper upon it, almost too quiet to hear at first.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I warned you didn't I child,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A soft raspy voice taunted.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;I told you what I would do if you ever left me, your are mine, your soul is mine, I have chosen you as my pet, run as you might, your only home is in my dark dwelling.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The voice sounded angry.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;YOU BASTARD!&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Silvereyes screamed into the night. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;I want nothing to do with you, why must you do this to me! I am NOT a child of darkness, I don't belong alone! IT CANNOT NOT BE THIS WAY!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The voice was laughing.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->    <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, you have so much to learn,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  It began,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; but I warned you didn't I?  I decide your fate, I have chosen you and my decision will not change, it is my will to keep you for my own, my pet, you have no one but me, you let no one close but me, how many times must I show you what I can and will do to those you let close to you?&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The voice was closer.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Oh God why did she have to count, the endless list of damned names, of people she let close, and who were slaughtered by her hand.  Possessed by gods to do their bidding, she had kept running, hiding among loved ones, guilds that accepted her, among ones that became family. She thought she could actually get away this time, thought she was strong enough to resist him, and keep it from happening again, this from happening again, and run away from the madness, away from them, from him. From that voice she hated.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;You win, Let no more deaths me on my head, take me, and not them.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  she said, exhausted by emotion and possession, she leaned on her side and looked up, the blank face of her friend, her sister, stared back at her.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Haha, but you see child, I have already won,&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  That voice was talking again.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;long ago, but it is time, time for you to accept me. Do you finally accept your fate child?&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The voice, asked, mocking in its own way.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->         <br>
<br>
&quot;If it means no one else has to die,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She paused, passing her eyes across lifeless bodies of those before her</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;then yes, I accept you, I submit to you, and cast of anyone of this world, bring what dreams may come, I am done.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  and she lowered her head.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Suddenly the air grew dense and howled, throwing open the doors, of the hall, it reached to her, for her. Suddenly the world was filled with pain, the world was pain, agony, hate, blood, hate.  Memories of what had gone before, love, friendship, family, everything flashed, lightning blazed into the room, she wasn't on the floor anymore, she was flying, more flashing, love, friendship, hate, anger, pain. She slammed into a wall and darkness covered, darkness and silence. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Now, Rise my daughter of evil,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  the voice commanded,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; and cast off your past, you truly are mine now.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  If only that damned voice could smile.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
As you command, so shall I do father,&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She said.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Sylex, pulled  her blade from the body it had been driven into and wiped the blood on the tattered curtain on the wall, surveying the bloody scene she smiled, it was no longer her smile, she was cursed now, she could still remember everything, yes, remember love, friendship, family,  but no feeling came to her, it was nothing, as though her heart had been stripped from her and nothing was left but a  hole, and a desire to fill that hole with the blood of all.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;As you ask, so shall I do,&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She said as she replaced the sword to its sheath.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;My black heart is yours to command father, so be it.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  And she turned and left the room, the mansion, her home, filled with the bloody remains of her friends, her family, and her loved ones, no more would she let  people be hurt by her curse, she would stand alone, and heaven be damned, she would survive some how.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
